Genital diseases concomitant with endometriosis based on our data. There is constantly growing interest towards endometriosis due to its remaining a mystery for the researchers. Some of them call it the disease of civilization. The combination of endometriosis and different gynaecological diseases is often unsuspected and accidentally diagnosed. The author determines interesting relationships between the disease and uterine myoma, uterine and ovarian neoplasms, for a period of 5 years on 1994 laparotomies and histologically proved endometriosis in 413 cases. The established relationship is presented in the applied table. Through her findings the author looks forward to contributing to the variety of combinations, which this interesting disease, the endometriosis, is able to register.